<gco:CharacterString>Although estuarine nurseries along the norther GoM are dominated by Spartina vegetation, production from these estuaries can vary greatly.  Studies in Texas and Louisiana marshes have demonstrated that production is related to temperature, salinity, and access to emergent marsh vegetation.  We are currently developing a systems model that will simulate recruitment, growth, and emigration of brown shrimp. This data will be used to help validate the model</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:abstract>          <gmd:purpose>             <gco:CharacterString>The goal of this study is to examine the effects of differing temperature, salinity, and marsh surface flooding regimes on brown shrimp growth and mortality rates</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:purpose>          <gmd:status>
